1
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:28,320
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:36,070
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:42,180
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,990
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:50,060
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:55,720
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,940
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:03,220
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,890
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,920
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,280
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:22,360
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:26,020
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,350
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:33,790
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,040
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 40=

19
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:53,840
Qin'e,

20
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,640
any layoffs at your workplace?

21
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:56,840
Shush.

22
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,140
I plan to return to Beishan
in a couple of days.

23
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,800
Don't talk.

24
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:29,120
♪As time flows swiftly by♪

25
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:33,920
♪I only care for you♪

26
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:40,000
♪I'm willingly touched by your breath♪

27
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:47,360
♪How rare to find a true confidant♪

28
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:53,720
♪Losing life's strength
would be worth it♪

29
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:57,680
♪So I beg of you♪
(Nightfall Bar)

30
00:02:57,680 --> 00:03:01,960
♪Don't let me leave you♪

31
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,160
♪Except for you♪

32
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:09,400
♪I can't feel a trace of affection♪

33
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,320
Bravo.

34
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,840
Handsome guys and pretty girls.

35
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,840
Thanks to Mr. Zhang at Table 3

36
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:25,840
for the two bouquets!

37
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,760
Thanks to Mr. Chen at Table 5

38
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:32,040
for the three bouquets!

39
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:36,320
Thanks to Miss Lin at Table 15

40
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,200
for the two bouquets!

41
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:42,080
Alright, thank Mr. Cheng at Table 18

42
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:43,920
for the eight bouquets!

43
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,320
What a grand gesture!

44
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,920
Let's give another round of applause.

45
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:50,120
Make it louder!

46
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:53,200
Mr. Cheng, you're so generous.

47
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,800
I must toast you today.

48
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:55,640
Come on, sit.

49
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,600
Why still call me Mr. Cheng?

50
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:00,040
Just call me Cheng.

51
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:02,280
We're so close now.

52
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,320
No need to be so formal.

53
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,200
Cheng.

54
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:07,160
I'll drink first. To you.

55
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,800
The autographed photo

56
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,960
I promised you last time.

57
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:14,560
Leslie!

58
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,240
Is it really him?

59
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,960
Thank you, I love him so much!

60
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:20,000
Is this for me?

61
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:20,840
Of course.

62
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,440
I love him so much!

63
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,120
So, lately,

64
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,200
we're working on a film

65
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,720
with him.

66
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,000
If you have time,

67
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,840
come for a set visit.

68
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:30,960
I can visit the set?

69
00:04:31,340 --> 00:04:32,230
To see him?

70
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:33,450
- Of course.
- Really?

71
00:04:33,450 --> 00:04:35,630
Then, can I take a picture with him?

72
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:36,600
No problem.

73
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,440
Seriously?

74
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,520
Thanks, I really appreciate it.

75
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,000
So,

76
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,320
how will you thank me?

77
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,240
No more words.

78
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,560
Good fortune follows after Rémy Martin.

79
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,960
To Cheng.

80
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,040
Good luck always.

81
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:57,470
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

82
00:04:57,470 --> 00:04:58,320
Cheers.

83
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:11,280
Handsome,

84
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:12,400
do you want a fresh beer?

85
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,270
Ice cold.

86
00:06:13,270 --> 00:06:14,440
50% off for a dozen.

87
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:15,640
Only 50 yuan.

88
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,520
No, thanks. Let's go.

89
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:18,760
It's really tasty.

90
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:21,240
I can't drink any more, thanks.

91
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:24,240
Pretty, your congee is ready.

92
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,200
Thanks!

93
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,240
Take your time. Enjoy.

94
00:06:27,380 --> 00:06:28,240
Okay.

95
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,160
Long time no see.

96
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,040
Pretty,

97
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,160
do you want to try some wine?

98
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,000
It's chilled.

99
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,000
50% off for a dozen.

100
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,240
Only 50 yuan.

101
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,440
No, I'm good. Thanks.

102
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,040
Try some. It's good.

103
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,040
No, I'm good.

104
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,960
Enjoy.

105
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,120
What?

106
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,000
Do I have to drink?

107
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:52,280
Chu Jiahe.

108
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,600
Why look at me?

109
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,000
You've changed.

110
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,440
My belly's gotten bigger.

111
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,520
You're completely different now.

112
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,360
Before?

113
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,360
I've forgotten what I was like before.

114
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,720
Why are you doing this?

115
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,320
Then what should I do?

116
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,880
I've done all sorts of things
over the years.

117
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,120
I have to. I'm so unlucky.

118
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,520
I failed at everything

119
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:56,800
and just

120
00:07:57,840 --> 00:07:59,960
narrowed my path more and more.

121
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,520
It's narrower and narrower.

122
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:03,680
I have no connections left.

123
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,560
I've got nothing at all.

124
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,120
I'm telling you.

125
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,400
Don't look down on this job.

126
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,320
With this,

127
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,000
I have this.

128
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:29,680
Stop looking.

129
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,680
Drinks are on me tonight.

130
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:40,680
You haven't changed.

131
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,680
Not at all.

132
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,440
You must be doing really well now.

133
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:50,560
Not bad.

134
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,040
Not bad?

135
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:54,360
You've even got a brick phone.

136
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,040
What did I say?

137
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:57,680
A bright future ahead.

138
00:08:58,520 --> 00:08:59,360
Here.

139
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,920
No more drinks for me.

140
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,960
I have work tomorrow.

141
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:17,820
I...

142
00:09:17,820 --> 00:09:19,000
I should get going.

143
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,080
Are you free this weekend?

144
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,280
Why?

145
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,050
Come with me for a set visit.

146
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,360
What's a set visit?

147
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:35,960
It's just checking out a movie set.

148
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:39,200
What would I do there?

149
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:41,760
There are opportunities.

150
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,240
Job opportunities.

151
00:10:59,080 --> 00:10:59,920
Mom.

152
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:01,920
Mom!

153
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:03,800
I'm home!

154
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,760
Mr. Integrity is back!

155
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:18,720
Ms. Zhang.

156
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:20,840
Ms. Zhang!

157
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,280
Mr. Integrity is back!

158
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:25,200
Mr. Integrity is back.

159
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,760
Was that you calling?

160
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,680
You little rascal, you're sharp.

161
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,240
Come on, do it again.

162
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,320
Wimp, wimp!

163
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:39,800
Hongbing, you're back.

164
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:40,670
Mom.

165
00:11:40,670 --> 00:11:41,720
This little one is amazing.

166
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,560
He's a playful one.

167
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,080
Come.

168
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,920
You're back.

169
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:55,440
What happened?

170
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:00,400
He had a stroke
before the Spring Festival

171
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:04,280
and didn't receive treatment in time,

172
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:05,600
so he ended up like this.

173
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,200
Hongbing.

174
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:13,800
Why didn't you tell me?

175
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:17,360
Your wife was
in postpartum confinement then.

176
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,400
Your dad didn't let me tell you.

177
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:21,600
He didn't want to worry you two.

178
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:23,960
Here, have some water.

179
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,560
Slow down.

180
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:32,920
Did you just come back?

181
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:34,520
Where's your wife and kid?

182
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,200
Just me.

183
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:41,240
Have you eaten?

184
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:44,000
I'll make you some noodles.

185
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,240
Where's Ms. Zhang?

186
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:48,680
After your dad retired,

187
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:50,040
his pay dropped a lot.

188
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,560
And we had huge medical bills.

189
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:55,040
I can handle things myself.
No need for helpers.

190
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,400
Wait here.

191
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,080
Hongbing.

192
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:05,800
Dad.

193
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,400
I'm back.

194
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,520
♪Heaven, please bless us♪

195
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:21,120
♪My baby cries through the night♪

196
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:21,960
Mom.

197
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:22,920
Mom, I'll hold him.

198
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,560
This baby's crying is really exhausting.

199
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:25,420
Here, here.

200
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:26,350
Your mom will hold you.

201
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:29,440
When the baby's asleep tonight,

202
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:31,330
we'll post the written charm:

203
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:32,400
"Heaven, please bless us".

204
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:34,150
That's just superstitious nonsense.

205
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:35,880
The baby cries
because he needs something.

206
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:36,960
What's the use of that?

207
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,320
Then meet his needs.

208
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:42,000
This baby's crying is so bizarre.

209
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:42,840
No more crying.

210
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:44,560
I've had three kids,

211
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:46,600
and I've never seen
such a difficult baby.

212
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,960
This was passed down by our ancestors.

213
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:50,000
It's bound to work.

214
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,240
He's not that hard to handle.

215
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:54,160
See? He's not crying now.

216
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:57,600
Who's there?

217
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:02,120
Who are you?

218
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,160
I live upstairs.

219
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:05,440
This is Qin'e's package.

220
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:07,120
I picked it up for her.

221
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:08,400
Thanks.

222
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:09,560
No worries.

223
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:10,600
The small one is mine.

224
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:11,960
Come in for some water.

225
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:12,840
No, no, thanks.

226
00:14:12,980 --> 00:14:13,840
Thanks.

227
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,600
You're welcome.

228
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,040
Where's this from?

229
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,120
Shen...

230
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:23,920
What does it say?

231
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,040
Shenzhen. Open it.

232
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:27,240
Let's play.

233
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,600
Shenzhen is so far away.

234
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,880
Who's this guy?

235
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:40,920
He's so spirited.

236
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:42,680
A singer.

237
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:45,480
A singer?

238
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:48,000
(Qin'e: I'm doing well in Shenzhen.)
This singer

239
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,800
(There's everything here.)
sent you a gift.

240
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:51,970
(I wish you all the best. Jiahe)
You met at a show?

241
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:55,480
What's this?

242
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,800
Isn't this towel pretty?

243
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:01,680
This whole box
is full of stuff for the kid.

244
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:03,520
Who sent it?

245
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:05,640
A friend of mine.

246
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:09,000
I've heard people say

247
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,280
that folks living in Shenzhen now

248
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,520
are all really capable.

249
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:13,600
This friend must be quite something.

250
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:15,760
Just look at these things.

251
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,540
The workmanship, the stitching.

252
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:18,800
You can tell it wasn't cheap.

253
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,000
Can you read it?

254
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:22,800
Jiahe.

255
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:23,840
This, this...

256
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,240
This is a...

257
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:28,600
Things are a bit busy here.

258
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:30,960
I might be delayed for a couple of days.

259
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:32,840
Sorry about that.

260
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:35,520
Please handle things at home for me.

261
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:38,120
I understand.

262
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,440
Don't worry about things here.

263
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:42,840
Are Mom and Dad okay?

264
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:49,640
They're fine.

265
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:52,680
They said they miss the kid.

266
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:55,320
They want you two to come home

267
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,400
for the Spring Festival.

268
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,440
Okay.

269
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:00,240
Get some rest then.

270
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:02,160
You too.

271
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:24,680
(With the things Chu Jiahe sent,)

272
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:27,040
(she seems to be doing well.)

273
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:31,000
(She envies this woman's courage
to dream and act.)

274
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,320
(From the day)

275
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,440
(she first met Chu Jiahe,)

276
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,320
(Chu Jiahe has been)

277
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,080
(the distant, unreachable lady)

278
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:40,560
(of status,)

279
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,120
(while she is)

280
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:44,000
(always like a servant girl.)

281
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,680
(Later, Yi Qin'e would learn)

282
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:50,720
(that Chu Jiahe had always envied her.)

283
00:16:58,040 --> 00:16:59,520
Try talking to Qin'e again.

284
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:00,840
I tried.

285
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:02,960
I know her too well.

286
00:17:03,060 --> 00:17:03,920
Right now,

287
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:05,520
sending anyone else won't help.

288
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:07,280
Let her figure it out herself.

289
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,800
What's Qin'e doing here?

290
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:18,240
No idea.

291
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:22,240
She's come around.

292
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:40,880
Out of the way, out of the way!

293
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,720
(Caution)
Move, move!

294
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:44,680
This way, please.

295
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,400
Jiahe, over here.

296
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,080
One more take, and we're done.

297
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,480
The box office will be huge.

298
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:05,840
Mr. Cheng.

299
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:06,680
You're here.

300
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:11,560
Is this your boyfriend?

301
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:13,320
I don't have a boyfriend.

302
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:14,160
He's my classmate.

303
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,800
It's to broaden his horizons.

304
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:17,680
Cheng

305
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,200
has shot many blockbusters.

306
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:21,280
Cheng.

307
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:22,360
Mr. Cheng,

308
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:23,920
take us under your wing.

309
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:26,800
What can he do?

310
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:28,680
He studied opera before.

311
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,920
He can act, too.

312
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:32,840
Acting and opera
are two different things.

313
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:36,480
Director, why not let him audition?

314
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:37,800
Alright, Director.

315
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:38,680
Alright, come on.

316
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,280
Come on, get ready. Let's go.

317
00:18:40,840 --> 00:18:41,680
Camera ready.

318
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,200
Scene 102, Shot 12, Take 2.

319
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,040
Action.

320
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:46,840
- Ready.
- Get ready.

321
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:48,280
Three, two, one.

322
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:49,120
Jump.

323
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,080
Cut.

324
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:55,840
What are you doing?

325
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:57,200
How many takes has it been?

326
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,440
Can you do it or not?

327
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:01,200
Director, this spot is too tricky.

328
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:02,480
Look, it's all uneven.

329
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:03,560
I really did my best.

330
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:04,960
I don't want your best effort.

331
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,360
I want ability.

332
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:07,760
If you can't, get lost.

333
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:08,840
Get someone who can.

334
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:09,680
Fine.

335
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:11,160
I'll do it myself.

336
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:12,360
Come on,

337
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,640
your leg is limping.

338
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,320
You're not healed.

339
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:17,600
How can you act?

340
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:18,720
Director.

341
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:22,840
I can give it a shot.

342
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:36,040
Have you done this before?

343
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:39,880
You've got guts, kid.

344
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,200
These HK (China) guys
aren't easy to fool.

345
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:43,640
The guy just now

346
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:44,680
has been through a lot.

347
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:45,680
Even he's washed up.

348
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,160
Don't try to be a hero.

349
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:48,880
I'll give it a shot.

350
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:50,440
I won't force it.

351
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:33,100
- Is everyone ready?
- Ready.

352
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:34,520
Yes, Director.

353
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:37,240
Action.

354
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:39,360
Alright, here we go.

355
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:40,760
Camera, ready.

356
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:42,720
Come on. Action!

357
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:44,680
Ready?

358
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:46,960
One, two, three.

359
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:47,800
Jump.

360
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:53,560
Cut.

361
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:54,840
That's a wrap.

362
00:20:59,620 --> 00:21:00,480
Are you okay, bro?

363
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:01,320
I'm fine, I'm fine.

364
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:04,800
I'm fine.

365
00:21:25,660 --> 00:21:28,500
(Qinqiang opera: Hua Ting Xiang Hui)

366
00:21:33,620 --> 00:21:40,500
(Qinchuan Province
Qinqiang Opera Youth Troupe)

367
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:45,100
♪So, it's you♪

368
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:49,220
♪You came for me♪

369
00:21:49,220 --> 00:21:54,820
♪I wanted♪

370
00:22:03,660 --> 00:22:14,600
♪To greet you♪

371
00:22:17,460 --> 00:22:24,460
♪I truly fear;
what if the Wen family knows♪

372
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,040
What are you doing?

373
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:30,480
Troupe Leader,
I'm just offering incense.

374
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:31,840
That's a superstition.

375
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:34,640
Don't talk nonsense.

376
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:38,960
He doesn't get it.

377
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,280
Don't blame him.

378
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:45,580
♪I keep♪

379
00:22:45,580 --> 00:22:50,620
♪Calling for you♪

380
00:22:50,620 --> 00:22:56,780
♪Oh, my dear♪

381
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:00,680
Guo Chuizi.

382
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:02,600
Lots of people today.

383
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:04,610
Play it harder. Let's liven it up!

384
00:23:04,610 --> 00:23:05,480
Alright, alright!

385
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:06,440
Harder!

386
00:23:12,020 --> 00:23:12,880
What's wrong?

387
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:13,720
What are you doing?

388
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:16,720
It's all tuned up.

389
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,080
No sleeping on the job.

390
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:20,400
I'm not sleeping.
I'm listening to the opera.

391
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:32,340
♪You've mistaken me♪

392
00:24:09,580 --> 00:24:12,260
(Rose Song and Dance Troupe)

393
00:24:14,360 --> 00:24:15,280
Turn up the volume.

394
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:16,840
This is a competition.

395
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:18,750
Troupe Leader, it's already at max.

396
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:20,800
Look at their sound equipment.

397
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:22,440
Imported, all high-frequency horns.

398
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:23,720
No matter how loud we go,

399
00:24:23,720 --> 00:24:24,960
it's just a mosquito buzz.

400
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:25,680
I don't care.

401
00:24:25,690 --> 00:24:27,400
You're the sound engineer.
You handle this.

402
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,480
Troupe Leader,
you're just messing with me.

403
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,280
I can't work miracles.

404
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:34,040
This is worse than my home stereo.

405
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:35,410
Why didn't you say so sooner?

406
00:24:35,420 --> 00:24:37,520
If you'd brought your stereo,
we would've been fine.

407
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:39,400
Troupe Leader, you're hilarious.

408
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:40,850
With what we're paid,

409
00:24:40,860 --> 00:24:42,320
how could I throw in my sound system?

410
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,120
If Lili hadn't insisted

411
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:45,520
on keeping a stable job as backup,

412
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:46,720
I'd have quit ages ago.

413
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,630
Let me tell you.

414
00:24:47,630 --> 00:24:49,240
That stall keeps us swamped.

415
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,100
Give it to me.

416
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:50,990
What?

417
00:24:50,990 --> 00:24:51,840
Your cigarettes.

418
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:54,480
Guo.

419
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:55,680
Guo!

420
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:57,080
Harder!

421
00:24:58,040 --> 00:24:59,320
That's my cigarette.

422
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,040
Troupe Leader.

423
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:03,040
Those legs are barely covered.

424
00:25:03,050 --> 00:25:04,370
And they have the nerve to dance?

425
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:05,920
Go away!

426
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:07,320
What do you know?

427
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,880
People watch this kind of show

428
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,880
for that Western flair.

429
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:26,640
Sir.

430
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:28,320
Sir,

431
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:29,760
have a smoke.

432
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:32,640
We're right across from you.

433
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:33,880
We're in this together.

434
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,440
Could you keep it down a bit?

435
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,280
Keep it down.

436
00:26:04,580 --> 00:26:05,540
♪I passed the exam♪

437
00:26:05,740 --> 00:26:08,580
♪On the Double Ninth Festival,
I sent a letter home♪

438
00:26:08,980 --> 00:26:11,180
♪If you don't mention the letter,
I'll let it slide♪

439
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:12,860
♪That letter enrages me♪

440
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:14,200
Guo Chuizi.

441
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:15,720
Where's Hu Sanyuan?

442
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:16,640
No idea.

443
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,240
Cut. Let's change it.

444
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:21,080
Play Qin Wang Po Zhen!

445
00:26:21,440 --> 00:26:22,280
Make a scene!

446
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:23,960
Play it harder!

447
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,440
Harder!

448
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:44,760
You look great.

449
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:48,200
Uncle, I'm a bit nervous.

450
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,360
Why?

451
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:53,040
You've been on bigger stages.

452
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:54,600
After all these years,

453
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:55,600
why be nervous?

454
00:26:58,800 --> 00:26:59,640
What's wrong?

455
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:01,640
I remembered what you told me.

456
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:04,360
You said that now, for me,

457
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:06,160
singing opera is like herding sheep.

458
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,640
When did I ever say that to you?

459
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:21,640
(Black Rose Song and Dance Troupe)
Everyone,

460
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:23,320
this is the show we bring you today.

461
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:25,040
We hope you enjoy it!

462
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:26,040
Everyone!

463
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,040
Yi Qin'e

464
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:29,640
will soon perform Bai She Zhuan for you!

465
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:32,120
In just three minutes,

466
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:35,120
your beloved Yi Qin'e

467
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:37,600
will bring you Bai She Zhuan.

468
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:39,640
Come and watch Bai She Zhuan!

469
00:27:40,120 --> 00:27:41,920
Yi Qin'e is here!

470
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:44,640
She's bringing you Bai She Zhuan!

471
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:46,440
Bai She Zhuan!

472
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:51,760
People used to go to the fair
and catch the big opera.

473
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,720
But times have changed.

474
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:55,760
The wind is picking up.

475
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:57,360
It looks like rain.

476
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:58,360
Can we perform today?

477
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,400
We'll have to speed it up

478
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,560
and cut

479
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:02,520
unnecessary parts.

480
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,560
Don't.

481
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:06,440
Or the audience won't follow.

482
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:08,320
With all this sand blowing,

483
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:10,520
do you want them eating dirt
or watching the show?

484
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:14,200
They haven't had a show
this good in years.

485
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,680
The audience came for the play.

486
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:17,040
We can't fool the audience.

487
00:28:18,080 --> 00:28:19,560
You're so full of yourself.

488
00:28:19,560 --> 00:28:20,720
Come and take a look.

489
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:23,040
Nowadays, at weddings and funerals,

490
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:24,920
everyone wants those new styles.

491
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:27,480
Who still watches
that old Qinqiang opera?

492
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:30,760
Qinqiang opera is ruined

493
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:31,800
by amateurs like you.

494
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:33,480
You're the biggest amateur of all!

495
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:37,520
Hu Sanyuan, you think you're so great?

496
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:39,400
It's definitely going to rain today.

497
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:40,600
You can take my word for it.

498
00:28:40,840 --> 00:28:42,600
Whether there's an audience or not,

499
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:44,600
if you can't play
the full-length opera through,

500
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:45,920
you're my grandson.

501
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,160
Forget about rain.

502
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:51,800
I'd finish
even if knives fell from the sky.

503
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,400
Grandson? Yeah, right.

504
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:59,040
The beautiful dance performance

505
00:28:59,040 --> 00:29:01,360
brought a feast for the eyes.

506
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,200
Stop the wind and rain.

507
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,480
Bring us favorable weather.

508
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:07,200
Let's give a scream for the performers!

509
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:11,840
Dance conveys

510
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:13,440
the spirit of the times

511
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:15,920
and enhances aesthetic appreciation.

512
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:19,760
We have

513
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,720
an evening show tonight,

514
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,720
with different music styles

515
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,720
and dance styles.

516
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:27,720
Welcome, everyone.

517
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:38,200
Bravo.

518
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:54,560
♪Out of nowhere, I just feel♪

519
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,440
I told you to keep it down.

520
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:06,280
Do you hear me?

521
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:08,000
They're performing opera back there.

522
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:10,720
How can everyone watch the opera?

523
00:30:19,080 --> 00:30:20,000
There's an opera there.

524
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:20,880
What are you doing?

525
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:27,560
Let's continue to enjoy
the music and dance.

526
00:30:28,140 --> 00:30:33,140
♪Last year♪

527
00:30:35,550 --> 00:30:40,620
♪On this day, inside this gate♪

528
00:30:42,980 --> 00:30:50,220
♪Her face blushed like peach blossoms♪

529
00:30:53,700 --> 00:30:58,820
♪Now, she's gone♪

530
00:31:03,260 --> 00:31:08,220
♪But peach blossoms still smile
in the spring breeze♪

531
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:13,160
I can drink.

532
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:15,160
Why did you take the drink for me?

533
00:33:16,960 --> 00:33:18,360
For you, I...

534
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:20,240
am willing.

535
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:22,920
Which direction?

536
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:25,080
Shall we turn left or right?

537
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:27,240
Here, here.

538
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,080
Here?

539
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:29,120
Here?

540
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:30,640
Yes.

541
00:33:31,320 --> 00:33:32,160
It's narrow there.

542
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:35,520
Just so you know,

543
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:37,240
if you stay,

544
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:38,560
I'll charge double for utilities.

545
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:39,440
I'm not staying.

546
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,680
I'm just dropping her off.

547
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:42,520
She's wasted. How's she getting up?

548
00:34:44,120 --> 00:34:45,960
Mr. Integrity is back.

549
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:48,080
Mr. Integrity is back.

550
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:49,240
Shut up.

551
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:51,560
All day long, so annoying.

552
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,840
You talk too much.

553
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:56,440
You think you're so great.

554
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:58,440
This parrot

555
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:01,080
was a gift to your father.

556
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:03,520
It's clever; it can say anything.

557
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:05,800
He's already learned the ending song

558
00:35:05,800 --> 00:35:07,200
of Yearning.

559
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:10,440
Come on, sing it.

560
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:13,400
Sing it.

561
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:14,840
I'll take you out to play later.

562
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:18,920
Not you. Eat your food.

563
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:21,920
You can't do anything right.

564
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:23,680
Full of crooked tricks.

565
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:26,280
Hongmei,

566
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:30,360
it's not up to your dad whether your son

567
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:32,240
can get into Xingshu Middle School.

568
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:34,080
Once you're out, the tea goes cold.

569
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:36,040
The principal

570
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:38,080
used to be your dad's subordinate.

571
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:40,920
He used to stop by every day.

572
00:35:40,920 --> 00:35:42,320
Now that your dad's retired,

573
00:35:42,320 --> 00:35:44,000
we can't even see a trace of him.

574
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:45,720
He hasn't come for half a year.

575
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,440
With your dad's situation,

576
00:35:47,440 --> 00:35:49,280
what do you expect him to do?

577
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:52,040
Back when the school was built,

578
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,800
it was approved by my dad.

579
00:35:53,900 --> 00:35:54,760
What?

580
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:56,760
Has he forgotten his benefactor?

581
00:35:57,600 --> 00:35:58,960
Alright, sis, drop it.

582
00:35:58,960 --> 00:35:59,840
Shut up.

583
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:01,560
Why are you back?

584
00:36:02,220 --> 00:36:03,080
Are you broke?

585
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:04,440
Did you come home for money?

586
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:06,760
Look at Dad now.

587
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:09,000
You're never around for real work

588
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:10,560
but quick to take advantage.

589
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:16,080
What do you want?

590
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,560
Are you eating or not?

591
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,200
You're just old.

592
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:20,680
Why are you so fragile now?

593
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:21,520
Dad, let's go.

594
00:36:21,860 --> 00:36:23,000
Let's go get some sun.

595
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:26,160
Then I'll eat.

596
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:31,880
You can sing, right?

597
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:33,560
Come on, sing it.

598
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:36,520
Hongbing.

599
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:38,920
Hongbing.

600
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,040
What, Dad?

601
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:43,880
Are you thirsty?

602
00:36:43,970 --> 00:36:44,920
I'll get you some water.

603
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,160
No?

604
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:51,600
Is your heart not well?

605
00:36:57,040 --> 00:36:57,960
I'll get it for you.

606
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:59,200
I'll take it out.

607
00:37:01,420 --> 00:37:02,860
(Current Savings Passbook)

608
00:37:02,860 --> 00:37:04,700
(Amount)

609
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:06,160
Take it.

610
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:09,240
Take it.

611
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:11,920
You're so impressive!

612
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:13,240
You even saved 5,000 yuan.

613
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:16,120
Take it.

614
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:18,680
I don't want it.

615
00:37:19,240 --> 00:37:20,080
No.

616
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:21,400
Take it.

617
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:22,920
I don't want it.

618
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:24,720
I'm not here for money.

619
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:26,200
Dad.

620
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:42,520
Dad.

621
00:37:44,840 --> 00:37:46,040
I want to live

622
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:49,160
a good life.

623
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:52,680
But somehow,

624
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:58,280
it all got so messed up.

625
00:38:06,420 --> 00:38:07,280
How did my life

626
00:38:07,280 --> 00:38:08,680
end up like this?

627
00:38:28,520 --> 00:38:29,600
I tried my best.

628
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:37,400
I really did.

629
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:04,440
As for singing technique,

630
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,720
it's actually very simple.

631
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:08,600
We need to open our mouths.

632
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:10,400
Breathe downwards.

633
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:12,520
Air should come from the Dantian.

634
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,880
We should also keep a smile.

635
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:18,000
Be full of emotion.

636
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:21,600
Truly imagine the person
you're closest to.

637
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:23,280
When will they return?

638
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:25,000
Feel it again.

639
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:33,800
♪Waiting for dawn at midnight♪

640
00:39:35,440 --> 00:39:37,360
Ready, sing.

641
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:44,800
♪Waiting for dawn at midnight♪

642
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:54,520
♪Longing for the spring breeze
in winter♪

643
00:39:56,560 --> 00:40:03,560
♪Longing for the Red Army to come♪

644
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:05,720
Mi Lan.

645
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:06,800
Here.

646
00:40:07,040 --> 00:40:08,160
You have a visitor.

647
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:16,920
Hua Caixiang, bring your things in.

648
00:40:17,600 --> 00:40:18,440
Coming.

649
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:23,880
I was just practicing a song.

650
00:40:26,120 --> 00:40:27,760
We're having a showcase.

651
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:30,120
I'm the lead singer.

652
00:40:30,920 --> 00:40:31,880
I'm also the lead.

653
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,240
That's great.

654
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:39,000
Guess what song I'm singing.

655
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:41,400
What?

656
00:40:42,720 --> 00:40:43,720
Ying Shan Hong.

657
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:46,840
This song always reminds me

658
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:50,040
of our days at the County Troupe.

659
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:53,720
How have you been?

660
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:56,670
Still teaching at the Children's Palace?

661
00:40:59,720 --> 00:41:00,720
I'm doing great.

662
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:04,400
The kids now are really sharp.

663
00:41:04,840 --> 00:41:06,000
They catch on right away.

664
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:07,520
Tell me about it.

665
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,560
When I ran a tutoring class
in the south,

666
00:41:10,560 --> 00:41:12,320
I discovered quite a few talented kids.

667
00:41:13,400 --> 00:41:15,840
One kid was especially clever.

668
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:17,920
I got him introduced to the TV station.

669
00:41:18,520 --> 00:41:20,960
He sang a cartoon theme song.

670
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:23,000
Now, he's a little child star.

671
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:28,160
I heard Laidi had a baby.

672
00:41:28,840 --> 00:41:29,680
She did.

673
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:31,280
The baby's six months old.

674
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:35,040
I couldn't make it to her wedding.

675
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:37,840
Oh, by the way,

676
00:41:38,160 --> 00:41:39,600
I have a dressing table at home.

677
00:41:41,240 --> 00:41:42,640
When it's delivered,

678
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:44,880
I'm already inside.

679
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:46,960
It's from Guangzhou.

680
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:48,160
It's new.

681
00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:49,720
I haven't even used it.

682
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:52,960
I'll have someone send it
to Laidi later.

683
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:54,840
Consider it her dowry.

684
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:56,760
No need.

685
00:41:57,920 --> 00:41:59,400
I also have a cashmere coat.

686
00:41:59,400 --> 00:42:00,360
It's from HK, China.

687
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:03,040
Really nice and new.

688
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:05,920
But I don't know if moths got to it.

689
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:07,720
I'll have someone check.

690
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,440
If there are no moths,

691
00:42:10,040 --> 00:42:11,440
I'll have it sent to you too.

692
00:42:13,160 --> 00:42:14,600
I have a watch at home too.

693
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:18,040
It's my husband's, Swiss-made.

694
00:42:19,160 --> 00:42:20,320
Anyway, he's locked up now.

695
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:21,640
He won't need it anymore.

696
00:42:22,680 --> 00:42:24,280
I'll send it over as well.

697
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:26,400
Give it to Sanyuan to wear.

698
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,600
Don't worry about me. I'm fine.

699
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:32,960
You two should take care, okay?

700
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:34,840
You have to hang in there.

701
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:36,640
Keep singing with heart.

702
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:38,120
Keep performing.

703
00:42:38,720 --> 00:42:40,440
This line of work has a real future.

704
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,560
You two,

705
00:42:44,680 --> 00:42:45,600
figure out a way

706
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:47,240
to start a troupe.

707
00:42:48,520 --> 00:42:49,760
Once I'm out,

708
00:42:50,040 --> 00:42:51,400
I'll be sticking with you guys.

709
00:42:54,760 --> 00:42:55,600
Alright.

710
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:58,320
I'll let you play the lead.

711
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

712
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:10,600
Do you know why people make wishes?

713
00:43:11,280 --> 00:43:13,800
The cake, wishes, and candles can give you

714
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:15,960
the courage to face another year.

715
00:43:16,960 --> 00:43:19,200
My performance was a huge success.

716
00:43:19,680 --> 00:43:21,040
As soon as I got on stage,

717
00:43:22,080 --> 00:43:23,360
I felt my energy come right back.

718
00:43:24,160 --> 00:43:25,480
I should've come back sooner.

719
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:27,480
I need to tell you something.

720
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:30,790
Where is it?

721
00:43:31,720 --> 00:43:32,700
What are you looking for?

722
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

723
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

724
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

725
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

726
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

727
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

728
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

729
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

730
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

731
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

732
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

733
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

734
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

735
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

736
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

737
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

738
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

739
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

740
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

741
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

742
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

